<br>
You're probably thinking of Conquest.<br>
<br>
Conquest was exploiting safe-area's (under a bridge) in ST to kill the 4th Warder (Back when few, if any, guilds had done so). GMs got wind of this exploiting, made there way to ST and in an effort to stop Conquest from killing the 4th Warder, just /kill'd it themselves. This in turn cause the script to activate, spawning the Kerafym (which buggely showed up as a giant Human), which then had to be /kill'd himself.<br>
<br>
This is just the basic premise of the story, there are so many different versions of it. For example, members of (the former) Conquest would probably tell you that they were not exploiting, but that the 4th Warder was /kill'd because the script was still buggy, and VI did not want it going live yet. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&amp;charname=Frawdo&amp;showAlts=false"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Frawdo Everhot</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
